      "writtenOn": "2021-04-09T01:15:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I didn\u0027t want to put any requirements on format of errors in base Store interface. Its UpdateSession says \"errors produced by the callback are returned as is\". It makes applying tags in UpdateSession kind of dodgy. So I removed it.\n\nUsers of Store are expected to understand that errors are transient. E.g. same way we do not wrap datastore.Get(...) errors as transient in the datastore library (except better, because Store is a mostly internal interface that will have ~\u003d2 implementations and only one user).",
      "parentUuid": "db15c062_6e817efe",
